# Errors & Debugging

## Error Types

| C# | JS/TS |
|----|-------|
| `throw new Exception("msg")` | `throw new Error("msg")` |
| `try/catch/finally` | same syntax |
| Custom: `class MyEx : Exception` | `class MyError extends Error` |
| `catch (SpecificException ex)` | no typed catch — check `instanceof` or error codes |
| `AggregateException` | `Promise.all` rejects with first error; use `Promise.allSettled` |

## Custom Errors

```typescript
class ConfigError extends Error {
  constructor(message: string) {
    super(message);
    this.name = 'ConfigError';
  }
}
```

## Async Errors

- Unhandled promise rejections crash Node (like unobserved `Task` exceptions).
- Always `await` or `.catch()` on promises.
- Express/Fastify: use error middleware (like ASP.NET exception filters).

## Debugging

| C# | Node |
|----|------|
| Visual Studio debugger | VS Code / Cursor debugger (F5) |
| `Debugger.Break()` | `debugger;` statement |
| `Console.WriteLine` | `console.log`, `console.error`, `console.debug` |
| Structured logging (Serilog) | `pino`, `winston` |
| `dotnet watch run` | `node --watch`, `tsx watch`, `nodemon` |

## `.vscode/launch.json` Pattern

Use `"type": "node"`, point `"program"` at entry file, set `"envFile": "${workspaceFolder}/.env"`.

## Applied AI: LLM Error Patterns

- Rate limits (429) → retry with exponential backoff
- Timeouts → `AbortSignal.timeout(ms)` or `AbortController`
- Invalid JSON from model → parse in try/catch, validate with Zod
- Log request id / model name, never log API keys
